Share this on WhatsAppSpread the loveAdamu Aliyu, chairman of the Miyyetti Allah Cattle Breeders’ Association of Nigeria (MACBAN) in Gwagwalada Area Council of Abuja, has been gunned down by bandits.
The bandits suddenly emerged from the bush and, opened fire on a truck that was conveying Aliyu and four others near Daku village in Dobi ward of the council on Thursday.
They were returning to Abuja from Niger then.
According to secretary of MACBAN, Mohammed Usman,  three persons were abducted while three others who sustained gunshot wounds were receiving treatment at a hospital in Abuja.
